rhouses the USA,nestled nicely in fifth in the medal table.\", \"from\": 726, \"to\": 853, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 726, \"end\": 739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999997825289265, \"rank\": 2.1718027272953942e-07, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 757, \"end\": 762, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.137988307186137e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 806, \"end\": 809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9758108383657195, \"rank\": 0.024490319033295127, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All times BST unless stated  Men's cycling road race - 10am  We are back out on the road for the first of this weekend's cycling races spanning 273km on a city circuit featuring plenty of gruelling climbs that both starts and finishes at the Place du Trocadero.\", \"from\": 855, \"to\": 1116, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 865, \"end\": 868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.200452193659563e-25, \"text\": \"BST\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The likes of Mathieu van der Poel, Remco Evenepoel, Wout van Aert and Mads Pedersen will hope to battle for gold.\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1231, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1131, \"end\": 1151, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"r